---
name: Inline
doclayout: true
notes:
  Inline items should be spaced out consistently with right margin directional flow.
  When there is a component that involves a group of inline items there should be additional CSS written
  in that component on the :last-child CSS pseudo-class to remove the right margin on the last item in the group.
  Wrapping inline items should make use of the Stack space settings.
order: 5
---
<h4 class="drizzle-h4">
  Example:
</h4>
<p>
  Inline items with xs spacing
</p>
<span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-xs">Cats</span><span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-xs">Dogs</span><span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-xs">Birds</span>

<p>
  Inline items with s spacing
</p>
<span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-s">Cats</span><span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-s">Dogs</span><span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-s">Birds</span>

<p>
  Inline items with m spacing
</p>
<span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-m">Cats</span><span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-m">Dogs</span><span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-m">Birds</span>

<p>
  Inline items with l spacing
</p>
<span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-l">Cats</span><span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-l">Dogs</span><span class="drizzle-Space-inline-right-l">Birds</span>

